    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen removing multiple plugins, only the last one that was removed gets actually displayed:\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b47c36bf-284f-4dd6-8ab4-21afca70b5b2\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Install two plugins with `vim.pack.add` (in this example I'm using `mini.hipatterns` and `nvim-lspconfig`)\n- `nvim --clean`\n- `:packdel mini.hipatterns nvim-lspconfig` (`vim.pack.del` can also be used if not on nightly)\n- No indication is given that `mini.hipatterns` has been removed (`g<` can still be pressed, but there's no indication to do so).\n\nThis happens with both the legacy message ui and ui2.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere are multiple solutions to this, which is why I didn't just open a PR and fix it myself:\n- These messages could be converted into progress messages.\n- `vim.pack.del()` could be changed to print a one line summary at the end (e.g. `vim.pack: Removed plugins: mini.hipatterns, nvim-lspconfig`)\n- It can just be \"fixed\" to show all lines.\n- These messages could be removed, and it is assumed that returning without an error constitutes success.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev+519-7d99104058",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-20T10:45:07Z",
    "closed_by": {
