        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> When removing multiple plugins, only the last one that was removed gets actually displayed:\n\nAll of them are displayed, just separately. And they are all visible in `:messages`.\n\n> This happens with both the legacy message ui and ui2.\n\nBut not with custom `vim.notify` (as it is what is used to show a notification) and maybe not with future versions of `ui2`.\n\n> Whenever a command performs a series of operations, it should usually be modeled as a `kind=progress` message.\n\nI don't think I agree with this. Progress report makes sense if there is a long running task to show that *something* is being done. Deleting plugins is virtually instant. **Edit**: Besides, by default it would have the same issue as described here. An extra `:messages` call is required to show all the intermediate progress steps.\n\nThe current approach seems fine to me and was deliberate. If there are strong opinions against it, I guess converting to a single `vim.notify` call that lists all plugins is a viable alternative.",
